review_blob: Hits the tongue sweet with ale yeasty esters.  Finishes with a metallic bite.  Smells like dust and steel.  A good Pale American Lager/Urban Malt Liqour.
Perfect balance with the very light roasted barley flavor and light lactose sweetness. Not a robust or dry stout and almost confusable with a porter.
beer_name: Denver Beer Sweet Teat Milk Stout

review_blob: Thought it to be quite crappy; hoppy acid bite and thats about it (clusters?).  No real steam yeast character detectable.
Little bit of chocolate and British hop zing, reminiscent of SKA Euphoria (but less chocolaty).  The bad-ass name is hard to pass up.

Aroma: Burnt vanilla, bark, cinnamon, oak, green bananas.
Taste: Spicy, main notes are pineapple and coffee which are very dissonant together... apparently there is no such thing as a black lambic for a reason Adam!

Aroma: Dusty leather, cedar sawdust, cigar box, antique books, very papery smelling...  Windex and urinal cake arrive later.  Taste:  Bitterness, dryness and sourness all balanced.   Sensation of bitting into a grapefruit peel, oak is strong yet tighly tucked in with esters and acids. 10 3 6 5 17

Aroma: Dank cedar swamp, slightly nutty.  Taste: Sauvignon Blanc and burning acid.  Too bitter/astringent and not tart like I hoped. This one doesnt "beat champagne at its own game" like other gueuzes.  Flavor improves as you drink and as it approaches room temp. 
* Bottle labeled 2005, cork labeled 2007.

Aroma: dry hop smells of centennial hops, not extreme like some RR or PP beers Taste: squarely imperial IPA flavor, bitterness strong not extreme.  Piny (simcoe?) presence.  Basically a Pliney clone but  less bubblegum, more hot spice and same pine bite.
Aroma:  Apple mush, barn wood, hints of clove  Taste: Wonderful brettanomyces character reminicent of tart fruit/sour candy.   Oak barrel favor expressed to a elegantly withheld level.
Aroma; light Pinappley American hop essence.  Some maple syrup/malt.   Taste; Carmel malt well balanced against toasty malt.  Quite hoppy to a level that almost overpowers the malt= a good thing.
Avery tap room 9/22/09.  Aroma; almonds and medium caramalts.  Taste;  THIS IS A PALE PORTER... some tiny funkiness?
Avery tap room 9/22/09.  Aroma;  citrus peel, yeast.  Taste;  frothy cream, apple cider, bread, orange juice, with a little frothy toothpaste.

Avery tap room 9/22/09.  Aroma; faint floral, great aroma slight smell of freshly opened plastic toys/peachy floral perfume.  Taste; Oh my god! sweet tarts, beautiful brett provides sensation like licking 9 volt, fizzy Sprite soda, sour lime.  (normally brett is labeled as horsey but this is froggy/pond scum.)
